(1517, 'εκδικησις', 1689, '1557', 'ἐκδίκησις', 'ekdikēsis', 9, 'vengeance, punishment, retributive justice, Lk. 21:22; Rom. 12:19; 2 Cor. 7:11; 1 Pet. 2:14; ἐκδίκησιν ποιεῖν, to vindicate, avenge, Lk. 18:7, 8; διδόναι ἐκδίκησιν, to inflict vengeance, Acts 7:24; 2 Thess. 1:8; Heb. 10:30*'),
(1518, 'εκδικος', 1690, '1558', 'ἔκδικος', 'ekdikos', 2, 'an avenger, one who inflicts punishment, Rom. 13:4; 1 Thess. 4:6*'),
(1519, 'εκδιωκω', 1691, '1559', 'ἐκδιώκω', 'ekdiōkō', 1, 'pr. to chase away, drive out; in NT to persecute, vex, harass, 1 Thess. 2:15*'),
