(1536, 'εκκλειω', 1710, '1576', 'ἐκκλείω', 'ekkleiō', 2, 'to shut out, exclude; to shut of, separate, insulate; Gal. 4:17; to leave no place for, eliminate, Rom. 3:27*'),
(1537, 'εκκλησια', 1711, '1577', 'ἐκκλησία', 'ekklēsia', 114, 'a popular assembly, Acts 19:32, 39, 41; in NT the congregation of the children of Israel, Acts 7:38; transferred to the Christian body, of which the congregation of Israel was a figure, the Church, 1 Cor. 12:28; Col. 1:18; a local portion of the Church, a local church, Rom. 16:1; a Christian congregation, 1 Cor. 14:4 '),
(1538, 'εκκλινω', 1712, '1578', 'ἐκκλίνω', 'ekklinō', 3, 'to deflect, deviate, Rom. 3:12; to decline or turn away from, avoid, Rom. 16:17; 1 Pet. 3:11'),
