(1541, 'εκκοπτω', 1716, '1581', 'ἐκκόπτω', 'ekkoptō', 10, 'to cut out; to cut off, Mt. 3:10; 5:30; met. to cut off an occasion, remove, prevent, 2 Cor. 11:12; to render ineffectual, Mt. 7:19; 18:8; Lk. 3:9; 12:7, 9; Rom. 11:22, 24; 1 Pet. 3:7* '),
(1542, 'εκκρεμαννυμι', 1717, '1582', 'ἐκκρεμάννυμι', 'ekkremannymi', 1, 'mid., to hang upon a speaker, fondly listen to, be earnestly attentive, Lk. 19:48*'),
