(1546, 'εκλεγομαι', 1721, '1586', 'ἐκλέγομαι', 'eklegomai', 22, 'to pick out; in NT to choose, select, Lk. 6:13; 10:42; in NT to choose out as the recipients of special favor and privilege, Acts 13:17; 1 Cor. 1:27 '),
(1547, 'εκλειπω', 1722, '1587', 'ἐκλείπω', 'ekleipō', 4, 'to fail, die out, Lk. 22:32; to come to an end, Heb. 1:12; to be defunct, Lk. 16:9; 23:45*'),
(1548, 'εκλεκτος', 1723, '1588', 'ἐκλεκτός', 'eklektos', 22, 'chosen out, selected; in NT chosen as a recipient of special privilege, elect, Col. 3:12; specially beloved, Lk. 23:35; possessed of prime excellence, exalted, 1 Tim. 5:21; choice, precious, 1 Pet. 2:4, 6 '),
(1549, 'εκλογη', 1724, '1589', 'ἐκλογή', 'eklogē', 7, 'the act of choosing out, election; in NT election to privilege by divine grace, Rom. 9:11; 11:5, 28; 1 Thess. 1:4; 2 Pet. 1:10; ἡ ἐκλογή, the elect, Rom. 11:7; ἐκλογῆς, equivalent to ἐκλεκτόν, by Hebraism, Acts 9:15*'),
