(1553, 'εκνευω', 1728, '1593', 'ἐκνεύω', 'ekneuō', 1, 'pr. to swim out, to escape by swimming; hence, generally, to escape, get clear of a place, Jn. 5:13; though ἐκνεύσας, in this place, may be referred to ἐκνεύω, to deviate, withdraw*'),
(1554, 'εκνηφω', 1729, '1594', 'ἐκνήφω', 'eknēphō', 1, 'pr. to awake sober after intoxication; met. to shake off mental bewilderment, to wake up from delusion and folly, 1 Cor. 15:34*'),
