(2438, 'ιωσηχ', 2738, '2501', 'Ἰωσήχ', 'Iōsēch', 1, 'Josech, pr. name, indecl., Lk. 3:26*'),
(2439, 'ιωσιας', 2739, '2502', 'Ἰωσίας', 'Iōsias', 2, 'Josiah, king of Judah (2 Ki. 22), Mt. 1:10, 11*'),
(2440, 'ιωτα', 2740, '2503', 'ἰῶτα', 'iōta', 1, 'iota; in NT used like the Hebrew/Aramaic yod, the smallest letter in the Hebrew/Aramaic alphabet, as an expression for the least or minutest part; a jot, Mt. 5:18*'),
(2441, 'καγω', 2743, '2504', 'κἀγώ', 'kagō', 84, 'and I, I also, but I, a crasis of καί and ἐγώ, dat., κἀμοί, acc., κἀμέ'),
(2442, 'καθα', 2745, '2505', 'καθά', 'katha', 1, 'can function as an adverb, just as, Mt. 27:10*'),
(2443, 'καθαιρεσις', 2746, '2506', 'καθαίρεσις', 'kathairesis', 3, 'tearing down, destruction, 2 Cor. 10:4, 8; 13:10*'),
(2444, 'καθαιρεω', 2747, '2507', 'καθαιρέω', 'kathaireō', 9, 'take or bring down, Mk. 15:36, 46; Lk. 1:52; 23:53; Acts 13:29; tear down, destroy, Lk. 12:18; Acts 13:19; 19:27; 2 Cor. 10:4*'),
(2445, 'καθαιρω', 2748, '2508', 'καθαίρω', 'kathairō', 1, 'to cleanse from filth; to clear by pruning, prune, Jn. 15:2; met. to cleanse from sin, make expiation'),
(2446, 'καθαπερ', 2749, '2509', 'καθάπερ', 'kathaper', 13, 'can function as an adverb, even as, just as, Rom. 3:4; 4:6; 9:13; 10:15; 11:8; 12:4; 1 Cor. 10:10; 12:12; 2 Cor. 1:14; 3:13, 18; 8:11; 1 Thess. 2:11; 3:6, 12; 4:5; Heb. 4:2*'),
(2447, 'καθαπτω', 2750, '2510', 'καθάπτω', 'kathaptō', 1, 'trans. to fasten or fit to; in NT equivalent to καθάπτομαι, to fix one’s self upon, fasten upon, take hold of, seize, Acts 28:3*'),
(2448, 'καθαριζω', 2751, '2511', 'καθαρίζω', 'katharizō', 31, 'to cleanse, render pure, purify, Mt. 23:25; Lk. 11:39; to cleanse from leprosy, Mt. 8:2, 3; 10:8; met. to cleanse from sin, purify by an expiatory offering, make expiation for, Heb. 9:22, 23; 1 Jn. 1:7; to cleanse from sin, free from the influence of error and sin, Acts 15:9; 2 Cor. 7:1; to pronounce ceremonially clean, Acts 10:15; 11:9 '),
(2449, 'καθαρισμος', 2752, '2512', 'καθαρισμός', 'katharismos', 7, 'ceremonial cleansing, purification, Lk. 2:22; 5:14; mode of purification, Jn. 2:6; 3:25; cleansing of lepers, Mk. 1:44; met. expiation, Heb. 1:3; 2 Pet. 1:9*'),
(2450, 'καθαρος', 2754, '2513', 'καθαρός', 'katharos', 27, 'clean, pure, unsoiled, Mt. 23:26; 27:59; met. clean from guilt, guiltless, innocent, Acts 18:6; 20:26; sincere, upright, virtuous, void of evil, Mt. 5:8; Jn. 15:3; clean ceremonially and morally, Lk. 11:41 '),
(2451, 'καθαροτης', 2755, '2514', 'καθαρότης', 'katharotēs', 1, 'cleanness; ceremonial purity, Heb. 9:13*'),
(2452, 'καθεδρα', 2756, '2515', 'καθέδρα', 'kathedra', 3, 'chair, seat, Mt. 21:12; 23:2; Mk. 11:15*'),
(2453, 'καθεζομαι', 2757, '2516', 'καθέζομαι', 'kathezomai', 7, 'to seat one’s self, sit down, Mt. 26:55; Lk. 2:46; Jn. 4:6; 1:20; 20:12; Acts 6:15; 20:9*'),
(2454, 'καθεξης', 2759, '2517', 'καθεξῆς', 'kathexēs', 5, 'in a continual order or series, successively, consecutively, Lk. 1:3; Acts 11:4; 18:23; ὁ, ἡ, καθεξῆς, succeeding, subsequent, Lk. 8:1; Acts 3:24*'),
(2455, 'καθευδω', 2761, '2518', 'καθεύδω', 'katheudō', 22, 'to sleep, be fast asleep, Mt. 8:24; 9:24; met. to sleep in spiritual sloth, Eph. 5:14; 1 Thess. 5:6; to sleep the sleep of death, to die, 1 Thess. 5:10 '),
(2456, 'καθηγητης', 2762, '2519', 'καθηγητής', 'kathēgētēs', 2, 'pr. a guide, leader; in NT a teacher, instructor, Mt. 23:10*'),
(2457, 'καθηκω', 2763, '2520', 'καθήκω', 'kathēkō', 2, 'to reach, extend to; καθήκει, impers. it is fitting, meet, Acts 22:22; τὸ καθῆκον, what is fit, right, duty; τὰ μὴ καθήκοντα, by litotes for what is abominable or detestable, Rom. 1:28*'),
(2458, 'καθημαι', 2764, '2521', 'κάθημαι', 'kathēmai', 91, 'to sit, be sitting, Mt. 9:9; Lk. 10:13; to be seated, 1 Cor. 14:30; to be enthroned, Rev. 18:7; to dwell, reside, Mt. 4:16; Lk. 1:79; 21:35 '),
(2459, 'καθημερινος', 2766, '2522', 'καθημερινός', 'kathēmerinos', 1, 'daily, day by day, Acts 6:1*'),
(2460, 'καθιζω', 2767, '2523', 'καθίζω', 'kathizō', 46, '(1) trans. to cause to sit, place; καθίζομαι, to be seated, sit, Mt. 19:28; Lk. 22:30; to cause to sit as judges, place, appoint, 1 Cor. 6:4; (2) intrans. to sit, sit down, Mt. 13:48; 26:36; to remain, settle, stay, continue, live, Lk. 24:49 '),
(2461, 'καθιημι', 2768, '2524', 'καθίημι', 'kathiēmi', 4, 'to let down, lower, Lk. 5:19; Acts 9:25; 10:11; 11:5*'),
(2462, 'καθιστημι', 2770, '2525', 'καθίστημι', 'kathistēmi', 21, 'also formed as καθιστάνω, to place, set, Jas. 3:6; to set, constitute, appoint, Mt. 24:45, 47; Lk. 12:14; to set down in a place, conduct, Acts 17:15; to make, render, or cause to be, 2 Pet. 1:8; pass. to be rendered, Rom. 5:19 '),
(2463, 'καθο', 2771, '2526', 'καθό', 'katho', 4, 'as, Rom. 8:26; according as, in proportion as, to the degree that, 2 Cor. 8:12; 1 Pet. 4:13*'),
(2464, 'καθολου', 2773, '2527', 'καθόλου', 'katholou', 1, 'on the whole, entirely, in general, altogether, completely; with a negative, not at all, Acts 4:18*'),
(2465, 'καθοπλιζω', 2774, '2528', 'καθοπλίζω', 'kathoplizō', 1, 'middle, to arm oneself (completely), Lk. 11:21*'),
(2466, 'καθοραω', 2775, '2529', 'καθοράω', 'kathoraō', 1, 'pr. to look down upon, in the NT to mark, perceive, discern, Rom. 1:20*'),
(2467, 'καθοτι', 2776, '2530', 'καθότι', 'kathoti', 6, 'as, just as, according as, in proportion as, Acts 2:45; 4:35; inasmuch as, Lk. 1:7; 19:9; Acts 2:24; 17:31*'),
(2468, 'καθως', 2777, '2531', 'καθώς', 'kathōs', 182, 'as, just as, in the manner that, Mt. 21:6; 26:24; how, in what manner, Acts 15:14; according as, Mk. 4:33; inasmuch as, Jn. 17:2; of time, when, Acts 7:17'),
(2469, 'καθωσπερ', 2778, '2531', 'καθώσπερ', 'kathōsper', 1, 'just as, exactly as, Heb. 5:4*'),
(2470, 'και', 2779, '2532', 'καί', 'kai', 9, '(1) and, Mt. 2:2, 3, 11; 4:22; (2) καί ... καί, both ... and; (3) as a cumulative particle, also, too, Mt. 5:39; Jn. 8:19; 1 Cor. 11:6; (4) emphatic, even, also, Mt. 10:30; 1 Cor. 2:10; in NT adversative, but, Mt. 11:19; also introductory of the apodosis of a sentence, Gal. 3:28; Jas. 2:4'),
(2471, 'καιαφας', 2780, '2533', 'Καϊάφας', 'Kaiaphas', 9, 'Caiaphas, pr. name, the high priest from A.D. 18-36, Mt. 26:3, 57; Lk. 3:2; Jn. 11:49; 18:13f., 24, 28; Acts 4:6*'),
(2472, 'καιν', 2782, '2535', 'Κάϊν', 'Kain', 3, 'Cain, pr. name, indecl., Heb. 11:4; 1 Jn. 3:12; Jude 11*'),
(2473, 'καιναμ', 2783, '2536', 'Καϊνάμ', 'Kainam', 2, 'Cainan, pr. name, indecl., Lk. 3:36, 37*');
