(2474, 'καινος', 2785, '2537', 'καινός', 'kainos', 41, 'new, recently made, Mt. 9:17; Mk. 2:22; new in species, character, or mode, Mt. 26:28, 29; Mk. 14:24, 25; Lk. 22:20; Jn. 13:34; 2 Cor. 5:17; Gal. 6:15; Eph. 2:15; 4:24; 1 Jn. 2:7; Rev. 3:12; novel, strange, Mk. 1:27; Acts 17:19; new to the possessor, Mk. 16:17; unheard of, unusual, Mk. 1:27; Acts 17:19; met. renovated, better, of higher excellence, 2 Cor. 5:17; Rev. 5:9 '),
(2475, 'καινοτης', 2786, '2538', 'καινότης', 'kainotēs', 2, 'newness, Rom. 6:4; 7:6*'),
(2476, 'καιπερ', 2788, '2539', 'καίπερ', 'kaiper', 5, 'though, although; Phil. 3:4; Heb. 5:8; 7:5; 12:17; 2 Pet. 1:12*'),
(2477, 'καιρος', 2789, '2540', 'καιρός', 'kairos', 85, 'pr. fitness, proportion, suitableness; a fitting situation, suitable place, 1 Pet. 4:17; a limited period of time marked by a suitableness of circumstances, a fitting season, 1 Cor. 4:5; 1 Tim. 2:6; 6:15; Tit. 1:3; opportunity, Acts 24:25; Gal. 6:10; Heb. 11:15; a limited period of time marked by characteristic circumstances, a signal juncture, a marked season, Mt. 16:3; Lk. 12:56; 21:8; 1 Pet. 1:11; a destined time, Mt. 8:29; 26:18; Mk. 1:15; Lk. 21:24; 1 Thess. 5:1; a season in ordinary succession, equivalent to ὥρα, Mt. 13:30; Acts 14:17; in NT a limited time, a short season, Lk. 4:13; simply, a point of time, Mt. 11:25; Lk. 13:1 '),
(2478, 'καισαρ', 2790, '2541', 'Καῖσαρ', 'Kaisar', 29, 'Caesar, pr. name'),
(2479, 'καισαρεια', 2791, '2542', 'Καισάρεια', 'Kaisareia', 17, 'Caesarea (1) Caesarea Philippi, Mt. 16:13; Mk. 8:27; (2) Caesarea Augusta, Acts 8:40'),
(2480, 'καιτοι', 2792, '2543', 'καίτοι', 'kaitoi', 2, 'and yet, though, although, Acts 14:17; Heb. 4:3*'),
(2481, 'καιτοιγε', 2793, '2544', 'καίτοιγε', 'kaitoige', 1, 'although indeed, and yet, Jn. 4:2*'),
(2482, 'καιω', 2794, '2545', 'καίω', 'kaiō', 11, 'to cause to burn, kindle, light, Mt. 5:15; pass. to be kindled, burn, flame, Lk. 12:35; met. to be kindled into emotion, Lk. 24:32; to consume with fire, Jn. 15:6; 1 Cor. 13:3 '),
(2483, 'κακει', 2795, '2546', 'κἀκεῖ', 'kakei', 10, 'crasis, and there, Mt. 5:23; 10:11; there also, Acts 17:13'),
(2484, 'κακειθεν', 2796, '2547', 'κἀκεῖθεν', 'kakeithen', 10, 'crasis, and there, Mk. 10:1; Acts 7:4; 14:26; 20:15; 21:1; 27:4, 12; 28:15; and then, afterwards, Acts 13:21'),
(2485, 'κακεινος', 2797, '2548', 'κἀκεῖνος', 'kakeinos', 22, 'crasis, and he, she, it; and this, and that, Mt. 15:18; 23:23; he, she, it also; this also, that also, Mt. 20:4'),
(2486, 'κακια', 2798, '2549', 'κακία', 'kakia', 11, 'malice, malignity, Rom. 1:29; Eph. 4:31; wickedness, depravity, Acts 8:22; 1 Cor. 5:8; in NT evil, trouble, calamity, misfortune, Mt. 6:34 '),
(2487, 'κακοηθεια', 2799, '2550', 'κακοήθεια', 'kakoētheia', 1, 'disposition for mischief, misfortune, malignity, Rom. 1:29*'),
(2488, 'κακολογεω', 2800, '2551', 'κακολογέω', 'kakologeō', 4, 'to speak evil of, revile, abuse, insult, Mk. 9:39; Acts 19:9; to address with offensive language, to treat with disrespect, Matt, 15:4; Mk. 7:10*'),
(2489, 'κακοπαθεια', 2801, '2552', 'κακοπάθεια', 'kakopatheia', 1, 'a state of suffering, affliction, trouble, in NT endurance in affliction, perseverance, Jas. 5:10*'),
(2490, 'κακοπαθεω', 2802, '2553', 'κακοπαθέω', 'kakopatheō', 3, 'to suffer evil or afflictions, 2 Tim. 2:9; to be afflicted, troubled, dejected, Jas. 5:13; in NT to show endurance in trials and afflictions, 2 Tim. 4:5*'),
(2491, 'κακοποιεω', 2803, '2554', 'κακοποιέω', 'kakopoieō', 4, 'to cause evil, injure, do harm, Mk. 3:4; Lk. 6:9; to do evil, commit sin, 1 Pet. 3:17; 3 Jn. 11*'),
(2492, 'κακοποιος', 2804, '2555', 'κακοποιός', 'kakopoios', 3, 'an evil-doer, 1 Pet. 2:12, 14; 4:15*'),
(2493, 'κακος', 2805, '2556', 'κακός', 'kakos', 50, 'bad, of a bad quality or disposition, worthless, corrupt, depraved, Mt. 21:41; 24:48; Mk. 7:21; wicked, criminal, morally bad; τὸ κακόν, evil, wickedness, crime, Mt. 27:23; Acts 23:9; deceitful, 1 Pet. 3:10; mischievous, harmful, destructive; τὸ κακόν, evil mischief, harm, injury, Tit. 1:12; afflictive; τὸ κακόν, evil, misery, affliction, suffering, Lk. 16;25 '),
(2494, 'κακουργος', 2806, '2557', 'κακοῦργος', 'kakourgos', 4, 'an evil-doer, malefactor, criminal, Lk. 23:32, 33, 39; 2 Tim. 2:9*'),
(2495, 'κακουχεω', 2807, '2558', 'κακουχέω', 'kakoucheō', 2, 'to torment, afflict, harass; pass. to be afflicted, be oppressed with evils, Heb. 11:37 13:3*'),
(2496, 'κακοω', 2808, '2559', 'κακόω', 'kakoō', 6, 'to harm, mistreat, cause evil to, oppress, Acts 7:6, 19; 12:1; 18:10; 1 Pet. 3:13; in NT to make angry, embitter, Acts 14:2*'),
(2497, 'κακως', 2809, '2560', 'κακῶς', 'kakōs', 16, 'ill, badly; physically ill, sick, Mt. 4:24; 8:16; grievously, vehemently, Mt. 15:22; wretchedly, miserably, Mt. 21:41; wickedly, reproachfully, Acts 23:5; wrongly, criminally, Jn. 18:23; amiss, Jas. 4:3 '),
(2498, 'κακωσις', 2810, '2561', 'κάκωσις', 'kakōsis', 1, 'ill treatment, affliction, oppression, misery, Acts 7:34*'),
(2499, 'καλαμη', 2811, '2562', 'καλάμη', 'kalamē', 1, 'the stalk of grain, straw, stubble, 1 Cor. 3:12*'),
(2500, 'καλαμος', 2812, '2563', 'κάλαμος', 'kalamos', 12, 'a reed, cane, Mt. 11:7; 12:20; Lk. 7:24; a reed in its various appliances, as, a wand, a staff, Mt. 27:29, 30, 48; Mk. 15:19, 36; a measuring-rod, Rev. 11:1; 21:15f.; a writer’s reed, 3 Jn. 13* '),
(2501, 'καλεω', 2813, '2564', 'καλέω', 'kaleō', 148, 'to call, call to, Jn. 10:3; to call into one’s presence, send for a person, Mt. 2:7; to summon, Mt. 2:15; 25:14; to invite, Mt. 22:9; to call to the performance of a certain thing, Mt. 9:13; Heb. 11:8; to call to a participation in the privileges of the Gospel, Rom. 8:30; 9:24; 1 Cor. 1:9; 7:18; to call to an office or dignity, Heb. 5:4; to name, style, Mt. 1:21; pass. to be styled, regarded, Mt. 5:9, 19 '),
(2502, 'καλλιελαιος', 2814, '2565', 'καλλιέλαιος', 'kallielaios', 1, 'pr. adj. productive of good oil; as subst. a cultivated olive tree, Rom. 11:24*'),
(2503, 'καλοδιδασκαλος', 2815, '2567', 'καλοδιδάσκαλος', 'kalodidaskalos', 1, 'teaching what is good; a teacher of good, Tit. 2:3*'),
(2504, 'καλοποιεω', 2818, '2569', 'καλοποιέω', 'kalopoieō', 1, 'to do well, do good, do what is right, 2 Thess. 3:13*'),
(2505, 'καλος', 2819, '2566,2570', 'καλός', 'kalos', 101, 'pr. beautiful; good, of good quality or disposition; fertile, rich, Mt. 13:8, 23; useful, profitable, Lk. 14:34; καλόν ἐστι[ν], it is profitable, it is well, Mt. 18:8, 9; excellent, choice, select, goodly, Mt. 7:17, 19; καλόν ἐστι[ν], it is pleasant, delightful, Mt. 17:4; just, full measure, Lk. 6:38; honorable, distinguished, Jas. 2:7; good, possessing moral excellence, worthy, upright, virtuous, Jn. 10:11, 14; 1 Tim. 4:6; τὸ καλόν, and τὸ καλόν ἔργον, what is good and right, a good deed, rectitude, virtue, Mt. 5:16; Rom. 7:18, 21; right, duty, propriety, Mt. 15:26; benefit, favor, Jn. 10:32, 33 '),
(2506, 'καλυμμα', 2820, '2571', 'κάλυμμα', 'kalymma', 4, 'a covering; a veil, 2 Cor. 3:13; met. a veil, a blind to spiritual vision, 2 Cor. 3:14, 15, 16*'),
(2507, 'καλυπτω', 2821, '2572', 'καλύπτω', 'kalyptō', 8, 'to cover, Mt. 8:24; Lk. 8:16; 23:30; to hide, conceal, Mt. 10:26; 2 Cor. 4:3; met. to cover, throw a veil of oblivion over, Jas. 5:20; 1 Pet. 4:8'),
(2508, 'καλως', 2822, '2573', 'καλῶς', 'kalōs', 37, 'well, rightly, suitable, with propriety, becomingly, 1 Cor. 7:37; 14:17; Gal. 4:17; 5:7; truly, justly, correctly, Mk. 12:32; Lk. 20:39; Jn. 4:17; appositely, Mt. 15:7; Mk. 7:6; becomingly, honorably, Jas. 2:3; well, effectually, Mk. 7:9, 37; καλῶς εἰπεῖν, to speak well, praise, applaud, Lk. 6:26; καλῶς ἔχειν, to be convalescent, Mk. 16:18; καλῶς ποιεῖν, to do good, confer benefits, Mt. 5:44; 12:12; to do well, act virtuously, Phil. 4:14 '),
(2509, 'καμηλος', 2823, '2574', 'κάμηλος', 'kamēlos', 6, 'a camel, Mt. 3:4; 23:24 '),
(2510, 'καμινος', 2825, '2575', 'κάμινος', 'kaminos', 4, 'a furnace, oven, kiln, Mt. 13:42, 50; Rev. 1:15; 9:2*'),
(2511, 'καμμυω', 2826, '2576', 'καμμύω', 'kammyō', 2, 'to shut, close the eyes, Mt. 13:15; Acts 28:27*'),
(2512, 'καμνω', 2827, '2577', 'κάμνω', 'kamnō', 2, 'to tire with exertion, labor to weariness; to be wearied, tired out, exhausted, be discouraged, Heb. 12:3; to labor under disease, be sick, Jas. 5:15*'),
(2513, 'καμπτω', 2828, '2578', 'κάμπτω', 'kamptō', 4, 'trans. to bend, inflect the knee, Rom. 11:4; Eph. 3:14 intrans. to bend, bow, Rom. 14:11; Phil. 2:10*'),
(2514, 'καν', 2829, '2579', 'κἄν', 'kan', 17, 'crasis, and if, Mk. 16:18; also if, Mt. 21:21; even if, if even, although, Jn. 10:38; if so much as, Heb. 12:20; also in NT simply equivalent to καί, as a particle of emphasis, by a pleonasm of ἄν, at least, at all events, Mk. 6:56; Acts 5:15; 2 Cor. 11:16'),
(2515, 'κανα', 2830, '2580', 'Κανά', 'Kana', 4, 'indecl. Cana, a town in Galilee, Jn. 2:1, 11; 4:46; 21:2*. See PhotoGuide.'),
(2516, 'καναναιος', 2831, '2580', 'Καναναῖος', 'Kananaios', 2, 'a Canaanite, Mt. 10:4; Mk. 3:18*'),
(2517, 'κανδακη', 2833, '2582', 'Κανδάκη', 'Kandakē', 1, 'Candace, pr. name, Acts 8:27*'),
(2518, 'κανων', 2834, '2583', 'κανών', 'kanōn', 4, 'a measure, rule; in NT prescribed range of action or duty, 2 Cor. 10:13, 15, 16; met. rule of conduct or doctrine, Gal. 6:16*'),
(2519, 'καπηλευω', 2836, '2585', 'καπηλεύω', 'kapēleuō', 1, 'pr. to be κάπηλος, a retailer; to peddle with; to corrupt, adulterate, 2 Cor. 2:17*'),
(2520, 'καπνος', 2837, '2586', 'καπνός', 'kapnos', 13, 'smoke, Acts 2:19; Rev. 8:4 '),
(2521, 'καππαδοκια', 2838, '2587', 'Καππαδοκία', 'Kappadokia', 2, 'Cappadocia, a district of Asia Minor, Acts 2:9; 1 Pet. 1:1*'),
(2522, 'καρδια', 2840, '2588', 'καρδία', 'kardia', 156, 'the heart, regarded as the seat of feeling, impulse, affection, desire, Mt. 6:21; 22:37; Phil. 1:7; the heart, as the seat of intellect, Mt. 13:15; Rom. 1:21; the heart, as the inner and mental frame, Mt. 5:8; Lk. 16:15; 1 Pet. 3:4; the conscience, 1 Jn. 3:20, 21; the heart, the inner part, middle, center, Mt. 12:40 '),
(2523, 'καρδιογνωστης', 2841, '2589', 'καρδιογνώστης', 'kardiognōstēs', 2, 'heart-knower, searcher of hearts, Acts 1:24; 15:8*'),
(2524, 'καρπος', 2843, '2590', 'καρπός', 'karpos', 66, 'fruit, Mt. 3:10; 21:19, 34; from the Hebrew, καρπὸς κοιλίας, fruit of the womb, offspring, Lk. 1:42; καρπὸς ὀσφύος, fruit of the loins, offspring, posterity, Acts 2:30; καρπὸς χειλέων, fruit of the lips, praise, Heb. 13:15; met. conduct, actions, Mt. 3:8; 7:16; Rom. 6:22; benefit, profit, Rom. 1:13; 6:21; reward, Phil. 4:17 '),
