(2752, 'κληρονομεω', 3099, '2816', 'κληρονομέω', 'klēronomeō', 18, 'pr. to acquire by lot; to inherit, obtain by inheritance; in NT to obtain, acquire, receive possession of, Mt. 5:5; 19:29; absol. to be heir, Gal. 4:30 '),
(2753, 'κληρονομια', 3100, '2817', 'κληρονομία', 'klēronomia', 14, 'an inheritance, patrimony, Mt. 21:38; Mk. 12:7; a possession, portion, property, Acts 7:5; 20:32; in NT a share, participation in privileges, Acts 20:32; Eph. 1:14; 5:5 '),
(2754, 'κληρονομος', 3101, '2818', 'κληρονόμος', 'klēronomos', 15, 'an heir, Mt. 21:38; Gal. 4:1; a possessor, Rom. 4:13; Heb. 11:7; Jas. 2:5 '),
(2755, 'κληρος', 3102, '2819', 'κλῆρος', 'klēros', 11, 'a lot, die, a thing used in determining chances, Mt. 27:35; Mk. 15:24; Lk. 23:34; Jn. 19:24; Acts 1:26; assignment, investiture, Acts 1:17; allotment, destination, Col. 1:12; a part, portion, share, Acts 8:21; 26:18; a constituent portion of the Church, 1 Pet. 5:3* '),
