(2768, 'κλυδωνιζομαι', 3115, '2831', 'κλυδωνίζομαι', 'klydōnizomai', 1, 'to be tossed by waves; met. to fluctuate in opinion, be agitated, tossed to and fro, Eph. 4:14*'),
