(2770, 'κνηθω', 3117, '2833', 'κνήθω', 'knēthō', 1, 'to scratch; to tickle, cause titillation; in NT mid. met. to procure pleasurable excitement for, to indulge an itching, 2 Tim. 4:3*'),
