(3991, 'πονηρια', 4504, '4189', 'πονηρία', 'ponēria', 7, 'pr. badness, bad condition; in NT evil disposition of mind, wickedness, mischief, malignity, Mt. 22:18; pl. πονηρίαι, wicked deeds, villanies, Mk. 7:23; Acts 3:26'),
(3992, 'πονηρος', 4505, '4190,4191', 'πονηρός', 'ponēros', 78, 'bad, unsound, Mt. 6:23; 7:17, 18; evil, afflictive, Eph. 5:16; 6:13; Rev. 16:2; evil, wrongful, malignant, malevolent, Mt. 5:11, 39; Acts 28:21; evil, wicked, impious, and τὸ πονηρόν, evil, wrong, wickedness, Mt. 5:37, 45; 9:4; slothful, inactive, Mt. 25:26; Lk. 19:22; ὁ πονηρός, the evil one, the devil, Mt. 13:19, 38; Jn. 17:15; evil eye, i.q. φθονερός envious, Mt. 20:15; Mk. 7:22; impl. covetous, Mt. 7:11 '),
(3993, 'πονος', 4506, '4192', 'πόνος', 'ponos', 4, 'labor, travail; pain, misery, anguish, Col. 4:13; Rev. 16:10, 11; 21:4*'),
(3994, 'ποντικος', 4507, '4193', 'Ποντικός', 'Pontikos', 1, 'belonging to or an inhabitant of Pontus, Acts 18:2*'),
(3995, 'ποντιος', 4508, '4194', 'Πόντιος', 'Pontios', 3, 'Pontius, pr. name, Acts 4:27'),
(3996, 'ποντος', 4509, '5117', 'Πόντος', 'Pontos', 1, 'Pontus, country of Asia Minor, Acts 2:9; 1 Pet. 1:1*'),
(3997, 'ποπλιος', 4511, '4196', 'Πόπλιος', 'Poplios', 2, 'Publius, pr. name, Acts 28:7, 8*'),
(3998, 'πορεια', 4512, '4197', 'πορεία', 'poreia', 2, 'a going, progress; a journey, travel, Lk. 13:22; from the Hebrew, way of life, business, occupation, Jas. 1:11*'),
(3999, 'πορευω', 4513, '4198', 'πορεύω', 'poreuō', 153, 'also listed as a deponent, πορεύομαι, to go, pass from one place to another, Mt. 17:27; 18:12; to go away, depart, Mt. 24:1; 25:41; Jn. 14:2, 3; trop. to go away, depart, from life, to die, Lk. 22:22; to go, pass on one’s way, journey, travel, Mt. 2:8, 9; Lk. 1:39; 2:41; πορεύομαι ὀπίσω, to go after, to become a follower or partisan, Lk. 21:8; or, to pursue after, be devoted to, 2 Pet. 2:10; from the Hebrew, to go or proceed in any way or course of life, live in any manner, Lk. 1:6; 8:14; Acts 9:31 '),
(4000, 'πορθεω', 4514, '4199', 'πορθέω', 'portheō', 3, 'to lay waste, destroy; impl. to harass, ravage, Acts 9:21; Gal. 1:13, 23*'),
(4001, 'πορισμος', 4516, '4200', 'πορισμός', 'porismos', 2, 'a providing, procuring; meton. source of gain, 1 Tim. 6:5, 6*'),
(4002, 'πορκιος', 4517, '4201', 'Πόρκιος', 'Porkios', 1, 'Porcius, pr. name, Acts 24:27*'),
(4003, 'πορνεια', 4518, '4202', 'πορνεία', 'porneia', 25, 'fornication, whoredom, Mt. 15:19; Mk. 7:21; Acts 15:20, 29; concubinage, Jn. 8:41; adultery, Mt. 5:32; 19:9; incest, 1 Cor. 5:1; lewdness, uncleanness, genr., Rom. 1:29; from the Hebrew, put symbolically for idolatry, Rev. 2:21; 14:8 '),
(4004, 'πορνευω', 4519, '4203', 'πορνεύω', 'porneuō', 8, 'to commit fornication, 1 Cor. 6:18; 10:8; Rev. 2:14, 20; from the Hebrew, to commit spiritual fornication, practise idolatry, Rev. 17:2; 18:3, 9* '),
(4005, 'πορνη', 4520, '4204', 'πόρνη', 'pornē', 12, 'a prostitute, a whore, harlot, an unchaste female, Mt. 21:31, 32; from the Hebrew, an idolatress, Rev. 17:1, 5, 15 '),
(4006, 'πορνος', 4521, '4205', 'πόρνος', 'pornos', 10, 'a catamite; in NT a fornicator, impure person, 1 Cor. 5:9, 10, 11; 6:9 '),
(4007, 'πορρω', 4522, '4206', 'πόρρω', 'porrō', 4, 'in advance, far advanced; far, far off, at a distance, Mt. 15:8; Mk. 7:6; Lk. 14:32, can be an improper prep. with the gen. The comparative form of the adverb appears as πορρώτερον at Lk. 24:28.*'),
(4008, 'πορρωθεν', 4523, '4207', 'πόρρωθεν', 'porrōthen', 2, 'from a distance, from afar, Heb. 11:13; at a distance, far, far off, Lk. 17:12*'),
(4009, 'πορφυρα', 4525, '4209', 'πορφύρα', 'porphyra', 4, 'purpura, murex, a species of shellfish that yielded the purple dye, highly esteemed by the ancients, its tint being a bright crimson; in NT a purple garment, robe of purple, Lk. 16:19; Rev. 18:12'),
(4010, 'πορφυροπωλις', 4527, '4211', 'πορφυρόπωλις', 'porphyropōlis', 1, 'a female seller of purple cloths, Acts 16:4*'),
