(4012, 'ποσακις', 4529, '4212', 'ποσάκις', 'posakis', 3, 'How many times? How often? Mt. 18:21; 23:37; Lk. 13:34*'),
(4013, 'ποσις', 4530, '4213', 'πόσις', 'posis', 3, 'drinking; drink, beverage, Jn. 6:55; Rom. 14:17; Col. 2:16*'),
(4014, 'ποσος', 4531, '4214', 'πόσος', 'posos', 27, 'How great? How much? Mt. 6:23; Lk. 16:5, 7; 2 Cor. 7:11; πόσῳ, adverbially before a comparative, How much? By how much? Mt. 7:11; 10:25; Heb. 10:29; of time, How long? Mk. 9:21; of number, pl. How many? Mt. 15:34; 16:9, 10'),
(4015, 'ποταμος', 4532, '4215', 'ποταμός', 'potamos', 17, 'a river, stream, Mk. 1:5; Acts 16:13; met. and allegor. Jn. 7:38; Rev. 22:1, 2; a flood, winter torrent, for χείμαρρος ποταμός, Mt. 7:25, 27 '),
(4016, 'ποταμοφορητος', 4533, '4216', 'ποταμοφόρητος', 'potamophorētos', 1, 'borne along or carried away by a flood or torrent, Rev. 12:15*'),
(4017, 'ποταπος', 4534, '4217', 'ποταπός', 'potapos', 7, 'Of what country? in NT equivalent to ποῖος, What? Of what manner? Of what kind or sort? Lk. 1:29; 7:37; denoting admiration, What? What kind of? How great? Mt. 8:27; Mk. 13:1'),
(4018, 'ποτε', 4537, '4218', 'ποτε', 'pote', 29, 'enclitic particle, once, some time or other, either past or future; formerly, Jn. 9:13; at length, Lk. 22:32; at any time, ever, Eph. 5:29; Heb. 2:1; intensive after interrogatives, ever, 1 Cor. 9:7; Heb. 1:5'),
(4019, 'ποτερον', 4538, '4220', 'πότερον', 'poteron', 1, 'interrogative of πότερος, α, ον, which never occurs in NT other than in this form, whether?, Jn. 7:17*'),
(4020, 'ποτηριον', 4539, '4221', 'ποτήριον', 'potērion', 31, 'a vessel for drinking, cup, Mt. 10:42; 23:25, 26; meton. the contents of a cup, liquor contained in a cup, Lk. 22:20; 1 Cor. 10:16; from the Hebrew, the cup or potion of what God’s administration deals out, Mt. 20:22, 23; Rev. 14:10 '),
(4021, 'ποτιζω', 4540, '4222', 'ποτίζω', 'potizō', 15, 'to cause to drink, give drink to, Mt. 10:42; met. 1 Cor. 3:2; Rev. 14:8; to water, irrigate, met. 1 Cor. 3:6, 7, 8 '),
(4022, 'ποτιολοι', 4541, '4223', 'Ποτίολοι', 'Potioloi', 1, 'Puteoli, a town of Italy, Acts 28:13*. See PhotoGuide.'),
(4023, 'ποτος', 4542, '4224', 'πότος', 'potos', 1, 'a drinking; a drinking together, drinking bout, 1 Pet. 4:3*'),
(4024, 'που', 4544, '4226', 'ποῦ', 'pou', 48, 'interrogative, where? In what place? direct, Mt. 2:2; Lk. 8:25; Jn. 1:39; indirect, Mt. 2:4; Jn. 1:40; whither, Jn. 3:8; 7:35; 13:36'),
