(4036, 'πραυς', 4558, '4239', 'πραύς', 'praus', 4, 'also spelled πρᾶος, meek, gentle, kind, forgiving, Mt. 5:5; mild, benevolent, humane, Mt. 11:29; 21:5; 1 Pet. 3:4*'),
(4037, 'πραυτης', 4559, '4240', 'πραύτης', 'prautēs', 11, 'also spelled πραότης, ητος, ἡ, meekness, mildness, forbearance, 1 Pet. 3:15; gentleness, kindness, Jas. 1:21; 3:13; Gal. 5:23 '),
(4038, 'πρεπω', 4560, '4241', 'πρέπω', 'prepō', 7, 'it becomes, it is fitting, it is proper, it is right, etc., and part. πρέπον, becoming, suitable, decorous, etc., Mt. 3:15; 1 Cor. 11:13; Eph. 5:3; 1 Tim. 2:10'),
(4039, 'πρεσβεια', 4561, '4242', 'πρεσβεία', 'presbeia', 2, 'eldership, seniority; an embassy, legation; a body of ambassadors, legates, Lk. 14:32; 19:14*'),
(4040, 'πρεσβευω', 4563, '4243', 'πρεσβεύω', 'presbeuō', 2, 'to be elder; to be an ambassador, perform the duties of an ambassador, 2 Cor. 5:20; Eph. 6:20*'),
(4041, 'πρεσβυτεριον', 4564, '4244', 'πρεσβυτέριον', 'presbyterion', 3, 'a body of old men, an assembly of elders; the Jewish Sanhedrin, Lk. 22:66; Acts 22:5; a body of elders in the Christian church, a presbytery, 1 Tim. 4:14*'),
(4042, 'πρεσβυτερος', 4565, '4245', 'πρεσβύτερος', 'presbyteros', 66, 'elder, senior; older, more advanced in years, Lk. 15:25; Jn. 8:9; Acts 2:17; an elder in respect of age, person advanced in years, 1 Tim. 5:1, 2; pl. spc. ancients, ancestors, fathers, Mt. 15:2; Heb. 11:2; as an appellation of dignity, an elder, local dignitary, Lk. 7:3; an elder, member of the Jewish Sanhedrin, Mt. 16:21; 21:23; 26:3, 47, 57, 59; an elder or presbyter of the Christian church, Acts 11:30; 14:23, et al. freq. '),
