(4047, 'πριν', 4570, '4250', 'πρίν', 'prin', 13, 'can function as a temporal conj. and an improper prep., before, of time, Mt. 26:34, 75; Mk. 14:72; πρὶν ἤ, sooner than, before, Mt. 1:18; Lk. 2:26'),
(4048, 'πρισκα', 4571, '4251', 'Πρίσκα', 'Priska', 3, 'see also Πρόσκιλλα, Prisca, pr. name, Rom. 16:3; 1 Cor. 16:19; 2 Tim. 4:19*'),
(4049, 'πρισκιλλα', 4572, '4252', 'Πρίσκιλλα', 'Priskilla', 3, 'Priscilla, pr. name, the diminutive form of Πρίσκα, the wife of Apollos, Acts 18:2, 18, 26*'),
(4050, 'προ', 4574, '4253', 'πρό', 'pro', 47, 'before, of place, in front of, in advance of, Mt. 11:10; Lk. 1:76; Acts 5:23; before, of time, Mt. 5:12; Lk. 11:38; before an infin. with the gen. of the article, before, before that, Mt. 6:8; Lk. 2:21; before, above, in preference, Jas. 5:12; 1 Pet. 4:8'),
(4051, 'προαγω', 4575, '4254', 'προάγω', 'proagō', 20, 'to lead, bring, or conduct forth, produce, Acts 12:6; 16:30; 25:26; intrans. to go before, to go first, Mt. 2:9; 21:9; Mk. 6:45; 1 Tim. 5:24; part. προάγων, ουσα, ον, preceding, previous, antecedent, 1 Tim. 1:18; Heb. 7:18; hence, in NT, trans. to precede, Mt. 14:22; to be in advance of, Mt. 21:31 '),
(4052, 'προαιρεω', 4576, '4255', 'προαιρέω', 'proaireō', 1, 'to prefer, choose; met. to purpose, intend considerately, 2 Cor. 9:7*'),
(4053, 'προαιτιαομαι', 4577, '4256', 'προαιτιάομαι', 'proaitiaomai', 1, 'pr. to charge beforehand; to convince beforehand, Rom. 3:9, since the charges in the case in question were drawn from Scripture.*'),
(4054, 'προακουω', 4578, '4257', 'προακούω', 'proakouō', 1, 'to hear beforehand or already, Col. 1:5*'),
(4055, 'προαμαρτανω', 4579, '4258', 'προαμαρτάνω', 'proamartanō', 2, 'to sin before; perf., to have already sinned, have sinned heretofore, 2 Cor. 12:21; 13:2*'),
(4056, 'προαυλιον', 4580, '4259', 'προαύλιον', 'proaulion', 1, 'the exterior court before an edifice, Mk. 14:68*'),
(4057, 'προβαινω', 4581, '4260', 'προβαίνω', 'probainō', 5, 'to go forward, advance, Mt. 4:21; Mk. 1:19; to advance in life, Lk. 1:7, 18; 2:36*'),
(4058, 'προβαλλω', 4582, '4261', 'προβάλλω', 'proballō', 2, 'to cast before, project; to put or urge forward, Acts 19:33; to put forth, as a tree its blossoms, etc., Lk. 21:30*'),
(4059, 'προβατικος', 4583, '4262', 'προβατικός', 'probatikos', 1, 'belonging or pertaining to sheep; ἡ προβατικὴ (πύλη), the sheep gate, Jn. 5:2*'),
(4060, 'προβατον', 4585, '4263', 'πρόβατον', 'probaton', 39, 'a sheep, Mt. 7:15; 9:36; 10:16; met. Mt. 10:6; 15:24 '),
