(4062, 'προβλεπω', 4587, '4265', 'προβλέπω', 'problepō', 1, 'to foresee; mid. to provide beforehand, Heb. 11:40*'),
(4063, 'προγινομαι', 4588, '4266', 'προγίνομαι', 'proginomai', 1, 'to be or happen before, be previously done or committed; προγεγονώς, bygone, previous, Rom. 3:25'),
(4064, 'προγινωσκω', 4589, '4267', 'προγινώσκω', 'proginōskō', 5, 'to know beforehand, to be previously acquainted with, Acts 26:5; 2 Pet. 3:17; to determine on beforehand, to foreordain, 1 Pet. 1:20; in NT, from the Hebrew, to foreknow, to appoint as the subject of future privileges, Rom. 8:29; 11:2* '),
(4065, 'προγνωσις', 4590, '4268', 'πρόγνωσις', 'prognōsis', 2, 'foreknowledge; in NT previous determination, purpose, Acts 2:23; 1 Pet. 1:2* '),
(4066, 'προγονος', 4591, '4269', 'πρόγονος', 'progonos', 2, 'born earlier, elder; a progenitor, pl. progenitors; parents, 1 Tim. 5:4; forefathers, ancestors, 2 Tim. 1:3*'),
(4067, 'προγραφω', 4592, '4270', 'προγράφω', 'prographō', 4, 'to write before, Rom. 15:4; Eph. 3:3; to make a subject of public notice; to set forth unreservedly and distinctly, Gal. 3:1; to designate clearly, Jude 4*'),
(4068, 'προδηλος', 4593, '4271', 'πρόδηλος', 'prodēlos', 3, 'previously manifest, before known; plainly manifest, very clear, prominently conspicuous, 1 Tim. 5:24, 25; Heb. 7:14*'),
(4069, 'προδιδωμι', 4594, '4272', 'προδίδωμι', 'prodidōmi', 1, 'to give before, precede in giving; Rom. 11:35*'),
(4070, 'προδοτης', 4595, '4273', 'προδότης', 'prodotēs', 3, 'a betrayer, traitor, Lk. 6:16; Acts 7:52; 2 Tim. 3:4*'),
(4071, 'προδρομος', 4596, '4274', 'πρόδρομος', 'prodromos', 1, 'a precursor, forerunner, one who advances to explore and prepare the way, Heb. 6:20*'),
(4072, 'προελπιζω', 4598, '4276', 'προελπίζω', 'proelpizō', 1, 'to have hope and confidence in a person or thing beforehand, Eph. 1:12*'),
(4073, 'προεναρχομαι', 4599, '4278', 'προενάρχομαι', 'proenarchomai', 2, 'to begin before a particular time, 2 Cor. 8:6, 10*'),
(4074, 'προερχομαι', 4601, '4281', 'προέρχομαι', 'proerchomai', 9, 'to go forwards, advance, proceed, Mt. 26:39; Mk. 14:35; Acts 12:10; to precede, go before any one, Lk. 22:47; to precede in time, be a forerunner or precursor, Lk. 1:17; to outgo, outstrip in going, Mk. 6:33; to travel in advance of any one, precede, 20:5, 13; 2 Cor. 9:5*'),
(4075, 'προετοιμαζω', 4602, '4282', 'προετοιμάζω', 'proetoimazō', 2, 'to prepare beforehand; in NT to appoint beforehand, Rom. 9:23; Eph. 2:10*'),
(4076, 'προευαγγελιζομαι', 4603, '4283', 'προευαγγελίζομαι', 'proeuangelizomai', 1, 'to announce joyful tidings beforehand, Gal. 3:8*'),
(4077, 'προεχω', 4604, '4284', 'προέχω', 'proechō', 1, 'to have or hold before; intrans. and mid. to excel, surpass, have advantage or preeminence, Rom. 3:9*'),
(4078, 'προηγεομαι', 4605, '4285', 'προηγέομαι', 'proēgeomai', 1, 'to go before, precede, lead onward; met. to endeavor to take the lead of, vie with, or, to give precedence to, to prefer, Rom. 12:10*'),
(4079, 'προθεσις', 4606, '4286', 'πρόθεσις', 'prothesis', 12, 'a setting forth or before; οἱ ἄρτοι τῆς προθέσεως, and ἡ πρόθεσις τῶν ἄρτων, the shewbread, the twelve loaves of bread, corresponding to the twelve tribes, which were set out in two rows upon the golden table in the sanctuary, Mt. 12:4; Mk. 2:26; Lk. 6:4; Heb. 9:2; predetermination, purpose, Acts 11:23; 27:13; Rom. 8:28; 2 Tim. 3:10 '),
(4080, 'προθεσμια', 4607, '4287', 'προθεσμία', 'prothesmia', 1, 'a time before appointed, set or appointed time, Gal. 4:2*'),
(4081, 'προθυμια', 4608, '4288', 'προθυμία', 'prothumia', 5, 'promptness, readiness, eagerness of mind, willingness, Acts 17:11; 2 Cor. 8:11, 12, 19; 9:2*'),
(4082, 'προθυμος', 4609, '4289', 'πρόθυμος', 'prothumos', 3, 'ready in mind, prepared, prompt, willing, Mt. 26:41; Mk. 14:38; τὸ πρόθυμον, i.q. ἡ προθυμία, readiness, eagerness of mind, Rom. 1:15*'),
(4083, 'προθυμως', 4610, '4290', 'προθύμως', 'prothumōs', 1, 'promptly, readily, willingly, heartily, cheerfully, 1 Pet. 5:2*'),
(4084, 'προιμος', 4611, '4406', 'πρόϊμος', 'proimos', 1, 'also spelled πρώϊμος, early, Jas. 5:7*'),
(4085, 'προιστημι', 4613, '4291', 'προίστημι', 'proistēmi', 8, 'to set before; met. to set over, appoint with authority; intrans. 2 aor. προὔστην, perf. προέστηκα, part. προεστώς, and mid. προίσταμαι, to preside, govern, superintend, Rom. 12:8; 1 Thess. 5:12; 1 Tim. 3:4, 5, 12; 5:17; mid. to undertake resolutely, to practise diligently, to maintain the practice of, Tit. 3:8, 14*'),
(4086, 'προκαλεω', 4614, '4292', 'προκαλέω', 'prokaleō', 1, 'to call out, challenge to fight; to provoke, irritate, with feelings of ungenerous rivalry, Gal. 5:26*'),
(4087, 'προκαταγγελλω', 4615, '4293', 'προκαταγγέλλω', 'prokatangellō', 2, 'to declare or announce beforehand, foretell, predict, Acts 3:18; 7:52*'),
(4088, 'προκαταρτιζω', 4616, '4294', 'προκαταρτίζω', 'prokatartizō', 1, 'to make ready, prepare, or complete beforehand, 2 Cor. 9:5*'),
(4089, 'προκειμαι', 4618, '4295', 'πρόκειμαι', 'prokeimai', 5, 'to lie or be placed before; met. to be proposed or set before, as a duty, example, reward, etc., Heb. 6:18; 12:1, 2; Jude 7; to be at hand, be present, 2 Cor. 8:12*'),
(4090, 'προκηρυσσω', 4619, '4296', 'προκηρύσσω', 'prokēryssō', 1, 'to announce publicly; in NT to announce before, Acts 13:24*'),
(4091, 'προκοπη', 4620, '4297', 'προκοπή', 'prokopē', 3, 'advance upon a way; met. progress, advancement, furtherance, Phil. 1:12, 25; 1 Tim. 4:15*'),
(4092, 'προκοπτω', 4621, '4298', 'προκόπτω', 'prokoptō', 6, 'pr. to cut a passage forward; to advance, make progress; to advance, as time, to be far spent, Rom. 13:12; met. to advance in wisdom, age, or stature, Lk. 2:52; seq. ἐν, to make progress or proficiency in, Gal. 1:14; προκόπτω ἐπὶ πλεῖον, to proceed or advance further, 2 Tim. 2:16; 3:9; προκόπτω ἐπὶ τὸ χεῖρον, to grow worse and worse, 2 Tim. 3:13*'),
(4093, 'προκριμα', 4622, '4299', 'πρόκριμα', 'prokrima', 1, 'previous judgment, prejudice, or, preference, partiality, 1 Tim. 5:21*'),
(4094, 'προκυροω', 4623, '4300', 'προκυρόω', 'prokyroō', 1, 'to sanction and establish previously, ratify and confirm before, Gal. 3:17*'),
(4095, 'προλαμβανω', 4624, '4301', 'προλαμβάνω', 'prolambanō', 3, 'to take before another, 1 Cor. 11:21; trop. to anticipate, do beforehand, Mk. 14:8; to take by surprise; pass. be taken unexpectedly, be overtaken, be taken by surprise, Gal. 6:1*'),
(4096, 'προλεγω', 4625, '4302,4277,4280', 'προλέγω', 'prolegō', 15, 'to tell beforehand, to foretell, Mt. 24:25; Acts 1:16; Rom. 9:29; 2 Cor. 13:2; Gal. 5:21; 1 Thess. 3:4 '),
(4097, 'προμαρτυρομαι', 4626, '4303', 'προμαρτύρομαι', 'promartyromai', 1, 'pr. to witness or testify beforehand; to declare beforehand, predict, 1 Pet. 1:11*'),
(4098, 'προμελεταω', 4627, '4304', 'προμελετάω', 'promeletaō', 1, 'to practise beforehand; to premeditate, Lk. 21:14*'),
(4099, 'προμεριμναω', 4628, '4305', 'προμεριμνάω', 'promerimnaō', 1, 'to be anxious or solicitous beforehand, to ponder beforehand, Mk. 13:11*'),
(4100, 'προνοεω', 4629, '4306', 'προνοέω', 'pronoeō', 3, 'to perceive beforehand, foresee; to provide for, 1 Tim. 5:8; mid. to provide for one’s self; by impl. to apply one’s self to a thing, practice, strive to exhibit, Rom. 12:17; 2 Cor. 8:21*'),
(4101, 'προνοια', 4630, '4307', 'πρόνοια', 'pronoia', 2, 'forethought; providence, provident care, Acts 24:2; provision, Rom. 13:14*'),
(4102, 'προοραω', 4632, '4275,4308', 'προοράω', 'prooraō', 4, 'to foresee, Acts 2:31; Gal. 3:8; to see before, Acts 21:29; in NT to have vividly present to the mind, to be mindful of, Acts 2:25*'),
(4103, 'προοριζω', 4633, '4309', 'προορίζω', 'proorizō', 6, 'to limit or mark out beforehand; to design definitely beforehand, ordain beforehand, predestine, Acts 4:28; Rom. 8:29, 30 '),
(4104, 'προπασχω', 4634, '4310', 'προπάσχω', 'propaschō', 1, 'to experience previously, of ill treatment, 1 Thess. 2:2*'),
(4105, 'προπατωρ', 4635, '4310', 'προπάτωρ', 'propatōr', 1, 'a grandfather; a progenitor, or ancestor, Rom. 4:1*'),
(4106, 'προπεμπω', 4636, '4311', 'προπέμπω', 'propempō', 9, 'to send on before; to accompany or attend out of respect, escort, accompany for a certain distance on setting out on a journey, Acts 15:3; 20:38; 21:5; to furnish with things necessary for a journey, Tit. 3:13; 3 Jn. 6'),
(4107, 'προπετης', 4637, '4312', 'προπετής', 'propetēs', 2, 'falling forwards; meton. precipitate, rash, Acts 19:36; 2 Tim. 3:4*'),
(4108, 'προπορευομαι', 4638, '4313', 'προπορεύομαι', 'proporeuomai', 2, 'to precede, go before, Acts 7:40; Lk. 1:76*'),
(4109, 'προς', 4639, '4314', 'πρός', 'pros', 700, 'from; met. for the benefit of, Acts 27:34; with a dative, near, by, at, by the side of, in the vicinity of, Mk. 5:11; Lk. 19:37; with an accusative, used of the place to which anything tends, to, unto, towards, Mt. 2:12; 3:5, 13; at, close upon, Mt. 3:10; Mk. 5:22; near to, in the vicinity of, Mk. 6:45; after verbs of speaking, praying, answering to a charge, etc., to, Mt. 3:15; 27:14; of place where, with, in, among, by, at, etc., Mt. 26:55; Mk. 11:4; Lk. 1:80; of time, for, during, Lk. 8:13; 1 Cor. 7:5; near, towards, Lk. 24:29; of the end, object, purpose for which an action is exerted, or to which any quality, etc., has reference, to, Jn. 4:35; Acts 3:10; 27:12; before an infin. with τό, in order to, that, in order that, Mt. 6:1; 13:30; 26:12; so as to, so that, Mt. 5:28; of the relation which any action, state, quality, etc., bears to any person or thing, in relation to, of, concerning, in respect to, with reference to, Mt. 19:8; Lk. 12:41; 18:1; 20:19; as it respects, as it concerns, with relation to, Mt. 27:4; Jn. 21:22, 23; according to, in conformity with, Lk. 12:47; 2 Cor. 5:10; in comparison with, Rom. 8:18; in attention to, Eph. 3:4; of the actions, dispositions, etc., exhibited with respect to any one, whether friendly, towards, Gal. 6:10; Eph. 6:9; or unfriendly, with, against, Lk. 23:12; Acts 23:30; after verbs signifying to converse, dispute, make a covenant, etc., with, Lk. 24:14; Acts 2:7; 3:25'),
(4110, 'προσαββατον', 4640, '4315', 'προσάββατον', 'prosabbaton', 1, 'the day before the sabbath, sabbath-eve, Mk. 15:42*'),
(4111, 'προσαγορευω', 4641, '4316', 'προσαγορεύω', 'prosagoreuō', 1, 'to speak to, accost, to name, declare, Heb. 5:10*'),
(4112, 'προσαγω', 4642, '4317', 'προσάγω', 'prosagō', 4, 'to lead or conduct to, bring, Lk. 9:41; Acts 16:20; to conduct to the presence of, to procure access for, 1 Pet. 3:18; to bring near; to near, in a nautical sense, Acts 27:27*'),
(4113, 'προσαγωγη', 4643, '4318', 'προσαγωγή', 'prosagōgē', 3, 'approach; access, admission, to the presence of any one, Rom. 5:2; Eph. 2:18; 3:12* '),
(4114, 'προσαιτεω', 4644, '0', 'προσαιτέω', 'prosaiteō', 1, 'to ask for in addition; to ask earnestly, beg; to beg alms, Jn. 9:8*'),
(4115, 'προσαιτης', 4645, '4319', 'προσαίτης', 'prosaitēs', 2, 'a beggar, mendicant, Mk. 10:46; Jn. 9:8*'),
(4116, 'προσαναβαινω', 4646, '4320', 'προσαναβαίνω', 'prosanabainō', 1, 'to go up further, Lk. 14:10*'),
(4117, 'προσαναλοω', 4649, '4321', 'προσαναλόω', 'prosanaloō', 1, 'to spend, Lk. 8:43*'),
(4118, 'προσαναπληροω', 4650, '4322', 'προσαναπληρόω', 'prosanaplēroō', 2, 'to fill up by addition; to supply deficiencies, 2 Cor. 9:12; 11:9*'),
(4119, 'προσανατιθημι', 4651, '4323', 'προσανατίθημι', 'prosanatithēmi', 2, 'occurs in the NT only as a middle, to lay upon over and above; mid. to put one’s self in free communication with, to confer with, Gal. 1:16; to confer upon, to propound as a matter of consideration, Gal. 2:6*'),
(4120, 'προσαπειλεω', 4653, '4324', 'προσαπειλέω', 'prosapeileō', 1, 'to threaten in addition, utter additional threats, Acts 4:21*'),
(4121, 'προσδαπαναω', 4655, '4325', 'προσδαπανάω', 'prosdapanaō', 1, 'to spend besides, expend over and above, Lk. 10:35*'),
(4122, 'προσδεομαι', 4656, '4326', 'προσδέομαι', 'prosdeomai', 1, 'to want besides or in addition, need, Acts 17:25*'),
(4123, 'προσδεχομαι', 4657, '4327', 'προσδέχομαι', 'prosdechomai', 14, 'to receive, accept; to receive, admit, grant access to, Lk. 15:2; to receive, admit, accept, and with οὐ, to reject, Heb. 11:35; to submit to, Heb. 10:34; to receive kindly, as a guest, entertain, Rom. 16:2; to receive, admit, as a hope, Acts 24:15; to look or wait for, expect, await, Mk. 15:43; Lk. 2:25 '),
(4124, 'προσδοκαω', 4659, '4328', 'προσδοκάω', 'prosdokaō', 16, 'to look for, be expectant of, Mt. 11:3; Lk. 7:19, 20; Acts 3:5; 2 Pet. 3:12, 13, 14; to expect, Acts 28:6; to wait for, Lk. 1:21; 8:40; Acts 10:24; 27:33; absol. to think, anticipate, Mt. 24:50; Lk. 12:46 '),
(4125, 'προσδοκια', 4660, '4329', 'προσδοκία', 'prosdokia', 2, 'a looking for, expectation, anticipation, Lk. 21:26; meton. expectation, what is expected or anticipated, Acts 12:11*'),
(4126, 'προσεαω', 4661, '4330', 'προσεάω', 'proseaō', 1, 'to permit an approach, Acts 27:7*'),
(4127, 'προσεργαζομαι', 4664, '4333', 'προσεργάζομαι', 'prosergazomai', 1, 'pr. to work in addition; to gain in addition in trade, Lk. 19:16*'),
(4128, 'προσερχομαι', 4665, '4334', 'προσέρχομαι', 'proserchomai', 86, 'to come or go to any one, approach, Mt. 4:3, 11; 5:1; 8:19, 25, et al. freq.; trop. to come or go to, approach, draw near, spiritually, Heb. 7:25; 11:6; 4:16; 1 Pet. 2:4; met. to assent to, accede to, concur in, 1 Tim. 6:3 ');
INSERT INTO `mounce` (`id`, `word`, `gkNr`, `strongs`, `lemma`, `transliteration`, `frequenceyCount`, `definition`) VALUES
(4129, 'προσευχη', 4666, '4335', 'προσευχή', 'proseuchē', 36, 'prayer, Mt. 17:21; 21:13, 22; Lk. 6:12; Acts 1:14; meton. a place where prayer is offered, an oratory, perhaps, Acts 16:13, 16 '),
(4130, 'προσευχομαι', 4667, '4336', 'προσεύχομαι', 'proseuchomai', 85, 'to pray, offer prayer, Mt. 5:44; 6:5, 6 '),
(4131, 'προσεχω', 4668, '4337', 'προσέχω', 'prosechō', 24, 'to have in addition; to hold to, bring near; absol. to apply the mind to a thing, to give heed to, attend to, observe, consider, Acts 5:35; Heb. 2:1; 2 Pet. 1:19; to take care of, provide for, Acts 20:28; when followed by ἀπό, μή, or μήποτε, to beware of, take heed of, guard against, Mt. 6:1; 7:15; to assent to, yield credence to, follow, adhere or be attached to, Acts 8:6, 10, 11; 16:14; to give one’s self up to, be addicted to, engage in, be occupied with, 1 Tim. 1:4, 3:8 '),
(4132, 'προσηλοω', 4669, '4338', 'προσηλόω', 'prosēloō', 1, 'to nail to, affix with nails, Col. 2:14*'),
(4133, 'προσηλυτος', 4670, '4339', 'προσήλυτος', 'prosēlytos', 4, 'pr. a newcomer, a stranger; in NT a proselyte, convert from paganism to Judaism, Mt. 23:15; Acts 2:11; 6:5; 13:43*'),
(4134, 'προσκαιρος', 4672, '4340', 'πρόσκαιρος', 'proskairos', 4, 'opportune, in NT continuing for a limited time, temporary, transient, Mt. 13:21; Mk. 4:17; 2 Cor. 4:18; Heb. 11:25*'),
(4135, 'προσκαλεω', 4673, '4341', 'προσκαλέω', 'proskaleō', 29, 'to call to one’s self, summon, Mt. 10:1; 15:10, 32; 18:2; to invite, Acts 2:39; to call to the performance of a thing, appoint, Acts 13:2; 16:10 '),
(4136, 'προσκαρτερεω', 4674, '4342', 'προσκαρτερέω', 'proskartereō', 10, 'to persist in adherence to a thing; to be intently engaged in, attend constantly to, Acts 1:14; 2:42; Rom. 13:6; to remain constantly in a place, Acts 2:46; to constantly attend upon, continue near to, be at hand, Mk. 3:9; Acts 8:13; 10:7 '),
(4137, 'προσκαρτερησις', 4675, '4343', 'προσκαρτέρησις', 'proskarterēsis', 1, 'perseverance, unremitting continuance in a thing, Eph. 6:18*'),
(4138, 'προσκεφαλαιον', 4676, '4344', 'προσκεφάλαιον', 'proskephalaion', 1, 'pr. a cushion for the head, pillow; also, a boat cushion, Mk. 4:38*'),
(4139, 'προσκληροω', 4677, '4345', 'προσκληρόω', 'prosklēroō', 1, 'pr. to assign by lot; in NT, to adjoin one’s self to, associate with, follow as a disciple, Acts 17:4*'),
(4140, 'προσκλινω', 4679, '4345', 'προσκλίνω', 'prosklinō', 1, 'pr. to make to lean upon or against a thing; met., to join one’s self to, follow as an adherent, Acts 5:36*'),
(4141, 'προσκλισις', 4680, '4346', 'πρόσκλισις', 'prosklisis', 1, 'pr. a leaning upon or towards a thing; met. a leaning towards any one, inclination of mind towards, partiality, 1 Tim. 5:21*'),
(4142, 'προσκολλαω', 4681, '4347', 'προσκολλάω', 'proskollaō', 2, 'pr. to glue to; to cleave closely to, Mk. 10:7; Eph. 5:31*'),
(4143, 'προσκομμα', 4682, '4348', 'πρόσκομμα', 'proskomma', 6, 'a stumbling, Rom. 9:32, 33; 1 Pet. 2:8; met. a stumbling block, an occasion of sinning, means of inducing to sin, Rom. 14:13; 1 Cor. 8:9; met. a moral stumbling, a shock to the moral or religious sense, a moral embarrassment, Rom. 14:20* '),
(4144, 'προσκοπη', 4683, '4349', 'προσκοπή', 'proskopē', 1, 'pr. a stumbling; offense; in NT an offense, shock, ground of exception, 2 Cor. 6:3*'),
(4145, 'προσκοπτω', 4684, '4350', 'προσκόπτω', 'proskoptō', 8, 'to dash against, to beat upon, Mt. 7:27; to strike the foot against, Mt. 4:6; Lk. 4:11; to stumble, Jn. 11:9, 10; met. to stumble at, to take offense at, Rom. 9:32; 14:21; 1 Pet. 2:8*'),
(4146, 'προσκυλιω', 4685, '4351', 'προσκυλίω', 'proskyliō', 2, 'to roll to or against, Mt. 27:60; Mk. 15:46*'),
(4147, 'προσκυνεω', 4686, '4352', 'προσκυνέω', 'proskyneō', 60, 'to do reverence or homage by kissing the hand; in NT to do reverence or homage by prostration, Mt. 2:2, 8, 11; 20:20; Lk. 4:7; 24:52; to pay divine homage, worship, adore, Mt. 4:10; Jn. 4:20, 21; Heb. 1:6; to bow one’s self in adoration, Heb. 11:21 '),
(4148, 'προσκυνητης', 4687, '4353', 'προσκυνητής', 'proskynētēs', 1, 'a worshiper, Jn. 4:23*'),
(4149, 'προσλαλεω', 4688, '4354', 'προσλαλέω', 'proslaleō', 2, 'to speak to, converse with, Acts 13:43; 28:20*'),
(4150, 'προσλαμβανω', 4689, '4355', 'προσλαμβάνω', 'proslambanō', 12, 'to take to one’s self, assume, take as a companion or associate, Acts 17:5; 18:26; to take, as food, Acts 27:33, 36; to receive kindly or hospitably, admit to one’s society and friendship, treat with kindness, Acts 28:2; Rom. 14:1, 3; 15:7; Phlm. 17; to take or draw to one’s self as a preliminary to an address of admonition, Mt. 16:22; Mk. 8:32* '),
(4151, 'προσλημψις', 4691, '4356', 'πρόσλημψις', 'proslēmpsis', 1, 'also spelled πρόσληψις, acceptance, Rom. 11:15*'),
(4152, 'προσμενω', 4693, '4357', 'προσμένω', 'prosmenō', 7, 'to continue, remain, stay in a place, 1 Tim. 1:3; to remain or continue with any one, Mt. 15:32; Mk. 8:2; Acts 18:18; to adhere to, Acts 11:23; met. to remain constant in, persevere in, Acts 13:43; 1 Tim. 5:5*'),
(4153, 'προσορμιζω', 4694, '4358', 'προσορμίζω', 'prosormizō', 1, 'to bring a ship to its station or to land; mid. to come to the land, Mk. 6:53*'),
(4154, 'προσοφειλω', 4695, '4359', 'προσοφείλω', 'prosopheilō', 1, 'to owe besides or in addition, Phlm. 19*'),
(4155, 'προσοχθιζω', 4696, '4360', 'προσοχθίζω', 'prosochthizō', 2, 'to be vexed or angry at, Heb. 3:10, 17*'),
(4156, 'προσπεινος', 4698, '4361', 'πρόσπεινος', 'prospeinos', 1, 'very hungry, Acts 10:10*'),
(4157, 'προσπηγνυμι', 4699, '4362', 'προσπήγνυμι', 'prospēgnymi', 1, 'to fix to, affix to, Acts 2:23*'),
(4158, 'προσπιπτω', 4700, '4363', 'προσπίπτω', 'prospiptō', 8, 'to fall or impinge upon or against a thing; to fall down to any one, Mk. 3:11; 7:25; to rush violently upon, beat against, Mt. 7:25'),
(4159, 'προσποιεω', 4701, '4364', 'προσποιέω', 'prospoieō', 1, 'to add or attach; mid. to attach to one’s self; to claim or arrogate to one’s self; to assume the appearance of, make a show of, pretend, Lk. 24:28*'),
(4160, 'προσπορευομαι', 4702, '4365', 'προσπορεύομαι', 'prosporeuomai', 1, 'to go or come to any one, Mk. 10:35*'),
(4161, 'προσρησσω', 4704, '4366', 'προσρήσσω', 'prosrēssō', 2, 'also spelled προσρήγνυμι, to break or burst upon, dash against, Lk. 6:48, 49*'),
(4162, 'προστασσω', 4705, '4367', 'προστάσσω', 'prostassō', 7, 'pr. to place or station at or against; to enjoin, command, direct, Mt. 1:24; 8:4; Mk. 1:44; to assign, constitute, appoint, Acts 17:26 '),
(4163, 'προστατις', 4706, '4368', 'προστάτις', 'prostatis', 1, 'a patroness, protectress, Rom. 16:2*'),
(4164, 'προστιθημι', 4707, '4369', 'προστίθημι', 'prostithēmi', 18, 'to put to or near; to lay with or by the side of, Acts 13:36; to add, adjoin, Mt. 6:27, 33; Lk. 3:20; Acts 2:41; from the Hebrew, denote continuation, or repetition, Lk. 19:11; 20:11, 12; Acts 12:3 '),
(4165, 'προστρεχω', 4708, '4370', 'προστρέχω', 'prostrechō', 3, 'to run to, or up, Mk. 9:15; 10:17; Acts 8:30*'),
(4166, 'προσφαγιον', 4709, '4371', 'προσφάγιον', 'prosphagion', 1, 'what is eaten besides; hence, genr. victuals, food, Jn. 21:5*'),
(4167, 'προσφατος', 4710, '4372', 'πρόσφατος', 'prosphatos', 1, 'pr. recently killed; hence, genr. recent, new, newly or lately made, Heb. 10:20*'),
(4168, 'προσφατως', 4711, '4373', 'προσφάτως', 'prosphatōs', 1, 'newly, recently, lately, Acts 18:2*'),
(4169, 'προσφερω', 4712, '4374', 'προσφέρω', 'prospherō', 47, 'to bear or bring to, Mt. 4:24; 25:20; to bring to or before magistrates, Lk. 12:11; 23:14; to bring near to, apply to, Jn. 19:29; to offer, tender, proffer, as money, Acts 8:18; to offer, present, as gifts, oblations, etc., Mt. 2:11; 5:23; Heb. 5:7; to offer in sacrifice, Mk. 1:44; Lk. 5:14; to offer up any one as a sacrifice to God, Heb. 9:25, 28; 11:17; mid. to bear one’s self towards, behave or conduct one’s self towards, to deal with, treat any one, Heb. 12:7 '),
(4170, 'προσφιλης', 4713, '4375', 'προσφιλής', 'prosphilēs', 1, 'friendly, grateful, acceptable, Phil. 4:8*'),
(4171, 'προσφορα', 4714, '4376', 'προσφορά', 'prosphora', 9, 'pr. a bringing to; in NT an offering, an act of offering up or sacrificing, Heb. 10:10, 14, 18; trop. Rom. 15:16; an offering, oblation, a thing offered, Eph. 5:2; Heb. 10:5, 8; a sacrifice, victim offered, Acts 21:26; 24:17*'),
(4172, 'προσφωνεω', 4715, '4377', 'προσφωνέω', 'prosphōneō', 7, 'to speak to, address, Mt. 11:16; Lk. 7:32; 13:12; to address, harangue, Acts 22:2; to call to one’s self, Lk. 6:13'),
(4173, 'προσχυσις', 4717, '4378', 'πρόσχυσις', 'proschysis', 1, 'an effusion, sprinkling, Heb. 11:28*'),
(4174, 'προσψαυω', 4718, '4379', 'προσψαύω', 'prospsauō', 1, 'to touch upon, touch lightly, with the dative, Lk. 11:46*'),
(4175, 'προσωπολημπτεω', 4719, '4380', 'προσωπολημπτέω', 'prosōpolēmpteō', 1, 'show partiality, Jas. 2:9*'),
