(5258, 'χλιαρος', 5950, '5513', 'χλιαρός', 'chliaros', 1, 'warm, tepid; lukewarm, Rev. 3:16*'),
(5259, 'χλωρος', 5952, '5515', 'χλωρός', 'chlōros', 4, 'pale green; green, verdent, Mk. 6:39; Rev. 8:7; 9:4; pale, sallow, Rev. 6:8*'),
(5260, 'χοικος', 5954, '5517', 'χοϊκός', 'choikos', 4, 'of earth, earthy, 1 Cor. 15:47, 48, 49*');
INSERT INTO `mounce` (`id`, `word`, `gkNr`, `strongs`, `lemma`, `transliteration`, `frequenceyCount`, `definition`) VALUES
(5261, 'χοινιξ', 5955, '5518', 'χοῖνιξ', 'choinix', 2, 'a choenix, an Attic measure for things dry, being the 48th part of a medimnus, consequently equal to the 8th part of the Roman modius, and nearly equivalent to about one quart, being considered a sufficient daily allowance for the sustenance of one man, Rev. 6:6 (2x)*'),
(5262, 'χοιρος', 5956, '5519', 'χοῖρος', 'choiros', 12, 'pr. a young swine; a swine, hog, or sow, Mt. 8:30, 31, 32 '),
(5263, 'χολαω', 5957, '5520', 'χολάω', 'cholaō', 1, 'pr. to be melancholy; used later as an equivalent to χολοῦμαι, to be angry, incensed, Jn. 7:23*'),
(5264, 'χολη', 5958, '5521', 'χολή', 'cholē', 2, 'the bile, gall; in NT a bitter ingredient, as wormwood, Mt. 27:34; χολὴ πικρίας, intense bitterness, met. thorough disaffection to divine truth, utter estrangement, Acts 8:23*'),
(5265, 'χοραζιν', 5960, '5523', 'Χοραζίν', 'Chorazin', 2, 'also spelled Χωραζίν and Χοραζείν, Chorazin, a town of Galilee, probably near Bethsaida and Capernaum, indecl., Mt. 11:21; Lk. 10:13*. See PhotoGuide.'),
(5266, 'χορηγεω', 5961, '5524', 'χορηγέω', 'chorēgeō', 2, 'to lead a chorus; at Athens, to defray the cost of a chorus; hence, to supply funds; to supply, furnish, 2 Cor. 9:10; 1 Pet. 4:11*'),
(5267, 'χορος', 5962, '5525', 'χορός', 'choros', 1, 'dancing with music, Lk. 15:25*'),
(5268, 'χορταζω', 5963, '5526', 'χορτάζω', 'chortazō', 16, 'pr. to feed or fill with grass, herbage, etc., to fatten; used of animals of prey, to satiate, gorge, Rev. 19:21; of persons, to satisfy with food, Mt. 14:20; 15:33, 37; met. to satisfy the desire of any one, Mt. 5:6 '),
(5269, 'χορτασμα', 5964, '5527', 'χόρτασμα', 'chortasma', 1, 'pasture, provender for cattle; food, provision, sustenance, for men, Acts 7:11*'),
(5270, 'χορτος', 5965, '5528', 'χόρτος', 'chortos', 15, 'an enclosure; pasture ground; fodder for beasts; in NT herbage, grass, Mt. 6:30; 14:19; a plant of corn, Mt. 13:26; Mk. 4:28 '),
(5271, 'χους', 5967, '5522', 'χοῦς', 'chous', 2, 'uncontracted form χόος, dust, acc., χοῦν, Mk. 6:11; Rev. 18:19*'),
(5272, 'χραομαι', 5968, '5530', 'χράομαι', 'chraomai', 11, 'to use, make use of, employ, Acts 27:17; 1 Cor. 7:31; to take advantage of, 1 Cor. 7:21; 9:12, 15; to use, to treat, behave towards, Acts 27:3; 2 Cor. 13:10 '),
(5273, 'χρεια', 5970, '5532', 'χρεία', 'chreia', 49, 'use; need, necessity, requisiteness, Eph. 4:29; Heb. 7:11; personal need, an individual want, Acts 20:34; Rom. 12:13; Phil. 2:25; 4:16, 19; χρείαν ἔχω, to need, require, want, Mt. 6:8; 14:16; Mk. 2:25; Jn. 2:25; ἐστὶ χρεία, there is need, Lk. 10:42; τὰ πρὸς τὴν χρείαν, necessary things, Acts 28:10; a necessary business, affair, Acts 6:3 '),
(5274, 'χρεοφειλετης', 5971, '5533', 'χρεοφειλέτης', 'chreopheiletēs', 2, 'debtor, Lk. 7:41; 16:5*'),
(5275, 'χρη', 5973, '5534', 'χρή', 'chrē', 1, 'impersonal verb, there is need or occasion, it is necessary, it is requisite; it becomes, it is proper, Jas. 3:10*'),
(5276, 'χρηζω', 5974, '5535', 'χρῄζω', 'chrēzō', 5, 'to need, want, desire, Mt. 6:32; Lk. 11:8; 12:30; Rom. 16:2; 2 Cor. 3:1*'),
(5277, 'χρημα', 5975, '5536', 'χρῆμα', 'chrēma', 6, 'anything useful, or needful; pl. wealth, riches, Mk. 10:23; Lk. 18:24; money, Acts 8:18, 20; 24:26; sg. price, Acts 4:37*'),
(5278, 'χρηματιζω', 5976, '5537', 'χρηματίζω', 'chrēmatizō', 9, 'to have dealings, transact business; to negotiate; to give answer on deliberation; in NT to utter a divine communication, Heb. 12:25; pass. to be divinely instructed, receive a revelation or warning from God, Mt. 2:12, 22; Lk. 2:26; Acts 10:22; Heb. 8:5; 11:7; intrans. to receive an appellation, Acts 11:26; Rom. 7:3*'),
(5279, 'χρηματισμος', 5977, '5538', 'χρηματισμός', 'chrēmatismos', 1, 'in NT a response from God, a divine communication, oracle, Rom. 11:4*'),
(5280, 'χρησιμος', 5978, '5539', 'χρήσιμος', 'chrēsimos', 1, 'useful, profitable, 2 Tim. 2:14*'),
(5281, 'χρησις', 5979, '5540', 'χρῆσις', 'chrēsis', 2, 'use, employment; manner of using, Rom. 1:26, 27*'),
(5282, 'χρηστευομαι', 5980, '5541', 'χρηστεύομαι', 'chrēsteuomai', 1, 'to be gentle, benign, kind, 1 Cor. 13:4*'),
(5283, 'χρηστολογια', 5981, '5542', 'χρηστολογία', 'chrēstologia', 1, 'bland address, fair speaking, Rom. 16:18*'),
(5284, 'χρηστος', 5982, '5543', 'χρηστός', 'chrēstos', 7, 'useful, profitable; good, agreeable, Lk. 5:39; easy, as a yoke, Mt. 11:30; gentle, benign, kind, obliging, gracious, Lk. 6:35; Eph. 4:32; Rom. 2:4; 1 Pet. 2:3; good in character, disposition, etc., virtuous, 1 Cor. 15:33* '),
(5285, 'χρηστοτης', 5983, '5544', 'χρηστότης', 'chrēstotēs', 10, 'pr. goodness, kindness, gentleness, Rom. 2:4; 11:22(3x); 2 Cor. 6:6; Gal. 5:22; Col. 3:12; Tit. 3:4; kindness shown, beneficence, Eph. 2:7; goodness, virtue, Rom. 3:12* '),
(5286, 'χρισμα', 5984, '5545', 'χρῖσμα', 'chrisma', 3, 'pr. anything which is applied by smearing; ointment; in NT an anointing, in the reception of spiritual privileges, 1 Jn. 2:20, 27*'),
(5287, 'χριστιανος', 5985, '5546', 'Χριστιανός', 'Christianos', 3, 'a Christian, follower of Christ, Acts 11:26; 26:28; 1 Pet. 4:16* '),
(5288, 'χριστος', 5986, '5547', 'Χριστός', 'Christos', 529, 'pr. anointed; ὁ Χριστός, the Christ, the Anointed One, i.e. Μεσσίας, the Messiah, Mt. 1:16, 17; Jn. 1:20, 25, 42; meton. Christ, the word or doctrine of Christ, 2 Cor. 1:19; 21; Eph. 4:20; Christ, a truly Christian frame of doctrine and affection, Rom. 8:10; Gal. 4:19; Christ, the Church of Christ, 1 Cor. 12:12; Christ the distinctive privileges of the Gospel of Christ, Gal. 3:27; Phil. 3:8; Heb. 3:14 '),
(5289, 'χριω', 5987, '5548', 'χρίω', 'chriō', 5, 'to anoint; in NT to anoint, by way of instituting to a dignity, function, or privilege, Lk. 4:18; Acts 4:27; 10:38; 2 Cor. 1:21; Heb. 1:9* '),
(5290, 'χρονιζω', 5988, '5549', 'χρονίζω', 'chronizō', 5, 'to spend time; to linger, delay, be long, Mt. 24:48; 25:5; Lk. 1:21; 12:45; Heb. 10:37*'),
(5291, 'χρονος', 5989, '5550', 'χρόνος', 'chronos', 54, 'time, whether in respect of duration or a definite point of its lapse, Mt. 2:7; 25:19 freq.; an epoch, era, marked duration, Acts 1:7; 1 Thess. 5:1 '),
(5292, 'χρονοτριβεω', 5990, '5551', 'χρονοτριβέω', 'chronotribeō', 1, 'to spend time, waste time, linger, delay, Acts 20:16*'),
(5293, 'χρυσιον', 5992, '5553', 'χρυσίον', 'chrysion', 12, 'gold, Heb. 9:4; 1 Pet. 1:7; Rev. 3:18; 21:18, 21; spc. gold when coined or manufactured; golden ornaments, 1 Tim. 2:9; 1 Pet. 3:3; Rev. 17:4; 18:16; gold coin, money, Acts 3:6; 20:33; 1 Pet. 1:18* '),
(5294, 'χρυσοδακτυλιος', 5993, '5554', 'χρυσοδακτύλιος', 'chrysodaktylios', 1, 'having rings of gold on the fingers, Jas. 2:2*'),
(5295, 'χρυσολιθος', 5994, '5555', 'χρυσόλιθος', 'chrysolithos', 1, 'chrysolite, a name applied by the ancients to all gems of a gold color; spc. the modern topaz, Rev. 21:10*'),
(5296, 'χρυσοπρασος', 5995, '5556', 'χρυσόπρασος', 'chrysoprasos', 1, 'a chrysoprase, a species of gem of a golden green color like that of a leek, Rev. 21:20*'),
(5297, 'χρυσος', 5996, '5557', 'χρυσός', 'chrysos', 10, 'gold, Mt. 2:11; 23:16, 17; meton. gold ornaments, 1 Tim. 2:9; gold coin, money, Mt. 10:9 '),
(5298, 'χρυσους', 5997, '5552', 'χρυσοῦς', 'chrysous', 18, 'golden, made of or adorned with gold, 2 Tim. 2:20; Heb. 9:4; Rev. 1:12, 13, 20; 9:13, 20, 21:15 '),
(5299, 'χρυσοω', 5998, '5557', 'χρυσόω', 'chrysoō', 2, 'to gild, overlay with gold, adorn or deck with gold, Rev. 17:4; 18:16*'),
(5300, 'χρως', 5999, '5559', 'χρώς', 'chrōs', 1, 'the skin; the body surface; Acts 19:12*'),
(5301, 'χωλος', 6000, '5560', 'χωλός', 'chōlos', 14, 'crippled in the feet, limping, halting, lame, Mt. 11:5; 15:30, 31; met. limping, weak, spiritually, Heb. 12:13; maimed, deprived of a foot, for ἀναπηρός, Mk. 9:45 '),
(5302, 'χωρα', 6001, '5561', 'χώρα', 'chōra', 28, 'space, room; a country, region, tract, province, Mk. 5:10; Lk. 2:8; a district, territory, suburbs, Mt. 8:28; meton. the inhabitants of a country, region, etc., Mk. 1:5; Acts 12:20; the country, as opposed to the city or town, Lk. 21:21; a field, farm, Lk. 12:16; Jn. 4:35 '),
(5303, 'χωρεω', 6003, '5562', 'χωρέω', 'chōreō', 10, 'to make room, either by motion or capacity; to move, pass, Mt. 15:17; to proceed, go on, 2 Pet. 3:9; to progress, make way, Jn. 8:37; trans. to hold as contents, contain, afford room for, Mk. 2:2; Jn. 2:6; 21:25; met. to give mental admittance to, to yield accordance, Mt. 19:11, 12; to admit to approbation and esteem, to regard cordially, 2 Cor. 7:2* '),
(5304, 'χωριζω', 6004, '5563', 'χωρίζω', 'chōrizō', 13, 'to divide, separate, Mt. 19:6; Mk. 10:9; Rom. 8:35, 39; to dissociate one’s self, to part, 1 Cor. 7:10, 11, 15; to withdraw, depart, Acts 1:4; 18:1, 2; Phlm. 15; to be aloof, Heb. 7:26* '),
(5305, 'χωριον', 6005, '5564', 'χωρίον', 'chōrion', 10, 'a place, spot; Mt. 26:36; Mk. 14:32; a field, farm, estate, domain, Jn. 4:5; Acts 1:18, 19(2x); 4:34; 5:3, 8; 28:7* '),
(5306, 'χωρις', 6006, '5565', 'χωρίς', 'chōris', 41, 'can function as an improper prep., apart, Jn. 20:7; apart from, parted from, Jn. 15:5; Jas. 2:18, 20, 26; alien from, Eph. 2:12; apart from, on a distinct footing from, 1 Cor. 11:11; apart from, distinct from, without the intervention of, Rom. 3:21, 28; 4:6; apart from the company of, independently of, 1 Cor. 4:8; Heb. 11:40 without the presence of, Heb. 9:28; without the agency of, Jn. 1:3; Rom. 10:14; without the employment of, Mt. 13:34; Mk. 4:34; Heb. 7:20, 21; 9:7, 18, 22; without, Lk. 6:49; Phil. 2:14; 1 Tim. 2:8; 5:21; Phlm. 14; Heb. 10:28; 11:6; 12:8, 14; clear from, Heb. 7:7; irrespectively of, Rom. 7:8, 9; without reckoning, besides, Mt. 14:21; 15:38; 2 Cor. 11:28; with the exception of, Heb. 4:15'),
(5307, 'χωρος', 6008, '5566', 'χῶρος', 'chōros', 1, 'Corus, or Caurus, the northwest wind; meton, the northwest quarter of the heavens, Acts 27:12*'),
(5308, 'ψαλλω', 6010, '5567', 'ψάλλω', 'psallō', 5, 'to move by a touch, to twitch; to touch, strike the strings or chords of an instrument; absol. to play on a stringed instrument; to sing to music; in NT to sing praises, Rom. 15:9; 1 Cor. 14:15; Eph. 5:19; Jas. 5:13* '),
(5309, 'ψαλμος', 6011, '5568', 'ψαλμός', 'psalmos', 7, 'impulse, touch of the chords of a stringed instrument; in NT a sacred song, psalm, Lk. 20:42; 24:44; Acts 1:20; 13:33; 1 Cor. 14:26; Eph. 5:19; Col. 3:16* '),
(5310, 'ψευδαδελφος', 6012, '5569', 'ψευδάδελφος', 'pseudadelphos', 2, 'a false brother, a pretend Christian, 2 Cor. 11:26; Gal. 2:4*'),
(5311, 'ψευδαποστολος', 6013, '5570', 'ψευδαπόστολος', 'pseudapostolos', 1, 'a false apostle, pretend minister of Christ, 2 Cor. 11:13*'),
(5312, 'ψευδης', 6014, '5571', 'ψευδής', 'pseudēs', 3, 'false, lying, Acts 6:13; Rev. 2:2; in NT pl. maintainers of religious falsehood, corrupters of the truth of God, Rev. 21:8*'),
(5313, 'ψευδοδιδασκαλος', 6015, '5572', 'ψευδοδιδάσκαλος', 'pseudodidaskalos', 1, 'a false teacher, one who teaches false doctrines, 2 Pet. 2:1*'),
(5314, 'ψευδολογος', 6016, '5573', 'ψευδολόγος', 'pseudologos', 1, 'false-speaking, 1 Tim. 4:2*'),
(5315, 'ψευδομαι', 6017, '5574', 'ψεύδομαι', 'pseudomai', 12, 'lie, Mt. 5:11; Acts 5:4; Rom. 9:1; 2 Cor. 11:31 '),
(5316, 'ψευδομαρτυρεω', 6018, '5576', 'ψευδομαρτυρέω', 'pseudomartyreō', 5, 'to bear false witness, give false testimony, Mt. 19:18; Mk. 10:19; 14:56, 57; Lk. 18:20*'),
(5317, 'ψευδομαρτυρια', 6019, '5577', 'ψευδομαρτυρία', 'pseudomartyria', 2, 'false witness, false testimony, Mt. 15:19; 26:59*'),
(5318, 'ψευδομαρτυς', 6020, '5575', 'ψευδόμαρτυς', 'pseudomartys', 2, 'a false witness, Mt. 26:60 (2x); 1 Cor. 15:15*'),
(5319, 'ψευδοπροφητης', 6021, '5578', 'ψευδοπροφήτης', 'pseudoprophētēs', 11, 'a false prophet, one who falsely claims to speak by divine inspiration, whether as a foreteller of future events, or as a teacher of doctrines, Mt. 7:15; 24:24; Mk. 13:22; Acts 13:6; 1 Jn. 4:1; Rev. 16:13 '),
(5320, 'ψευδος', 6022, '5579', 'ψεῦδος', 'pseudos', 10, 'falsehood, Jn. 8:44; Eph. 4:25; 2 Thess. 2:9, 11; 1 Jn. 2:21, 27; in NT religious falsehood, perversion of religious truth, false religion, Rom. 1:25; the practices of false religion, Rev. 14:15; 21:27; 22:15* '),
(5321, 'ψευδοχριστος', 6023, '5580', 'ψευδόχριστος', 'pseudochristos', 2, 'a false Christ, pretend Messiah, Mt. 24:24; Mk. 13:22*'),
(5322, 'ψευδωνυμος', 6024, '5581', 'ψευδώνυμος', 'pseudōnymos', 1, 'falsely named, falsely called, 1 Tim. 6:20*'),
(5323, 'ψευσμα', 6025, '5582', 'ψεῦσμα', 'pseusma', 1, 'a falsehood, lie; in NT untruthfulness, Rom. 3:7*'),
(5324, 'ψευστης', 6026, '5583', 'ψεύστης', 'pseustēs', 10, 'one who utters a falsehood, a liar, Jn. 8:44, 55; Rom. 3:4; 1 Tim. 1:10; Tit. 1:12; 1 Jn. 1:10; 2:4, 22; 4:20; 5:10* '),
(5325, 'ψηλαφαω', 6027, '5584', 'ψηλαφάω', 'psēlaphaō', 4, 'to feel, handle, Lk. 24:39; to feel or grope for or after, as persons in the dark, Acts 17:27; Heb. 12:18; 1 Jn. 1:1*'),
(5326, 'ψηφιζω', 6028, '5585', 'ψηφίζω', 'psēphizō', 2, 'to reckon by means of pebbles, compute by counters; hence genr. to compute, reckon, calculate, Lk. 14:28; Rev. 13:18*'),
(5327, 'ψηφος', 6029, '5586', 'ψῆφος', 'psēphos', 3, 'a small stone, pebble; a pebble variously employed, especially in a ballot; hence, a vote, suffrage, Acts 26:10; a pebble or stone; probably given as a token, Rev. 2:17 (2x)*'),
(5328, 'ψιθυρισμος', 6030, '5587', 'ψιθυρισμός', 'psithurismos', 1, 'a whispering; a calumnious whispering, gossip, 2 Cor. 12:20*'),
(5329, 'ψιθυριστης', 6031, '5588', 'ψιθυριστής', 'psithuristēs', 1, 'a whisperer; a whisperer, gossip, Rom. 1:29*'),
(5330, 'ψιχιον', 6033, '5589', 'ψιχίον', 'psichion', 2, 'a morsel, crumb, bit, Mt. 15:27; Mk. 7:28*'),
(5331, 'ψυχη', 6034, '5590', 'ψυχή', 'psychē', 103, 'breath; the principle of animal life; the life, Mt. 2:20; 6:25; Mk. 3:4; Lk. 21:19; Jn. 10:11; an inanimate being, 1 Cor. 15:45; a human individual, soul, Acts 2:41; 3:23; 7:14; 27:37; Rom. 13:1; 1 Pet. 3:20; the immaterial soul, Mt. 10:28; 1 Pet. 1:9; 2:11, 25; 4:19; the soul as the seat of religious and moral sentiment, Mt. 11:29; Acts 14:2, 22; 15:24; Eph. 6:6; the soul, as a seat of feeling, Mt. 12:18; 26:38; the soul, the inner self, Lk. 12:19 '),
(5332, 'ψυχικος', 6035, '5591', 'ψυχικός', 'psychikos', 6, 'pertaining to the life or soul; in NT animal, as distinguished from spiritual subsistence, 1 Cor. 15:44, 46; occupied with mere animal things, animal, sensual, 1 Cor. 2:14; Jas. 3:15; Jude 19*'),
(5333, 'ψυχος', 6036, '5592', 'ψῦχος', 'psychos', 3, 'cold, Jn. 18:18; Acts 28:2; 2 Cor. 11:27*'),
(5334, 'ψυχρος', 6037, '5593', 'ψυχρός', 'psychros', 4, 'cool, cold, Mt. 10:42; met. Rev. 3:15, 16*'),
(5335, 'ψυχω', 6038, '5594', 'ψύχω', 'psychō', 1, 'to breathe; to cool; pass. to be cooled; met. of affection, Mt. 24:12*'),
(5336, 'ψωμιζω', 6039, '5595', 'ψωμίζω', 'psōmizō', 2, 'pr. to feed by morsels; hence, genr. to feed, supply with food, Rom. 12:20; to bestow in supplying food, 1 Cor. 13:3*'),
(5337, 'ψωμιον', 6040, '5596', 'ψωμίον', 'psōmion', 4, 'a bit, morsel, mouthful, Jn. 13:26, 27, 30*'),
(5338, 'ψωχω', 6041, '5597', 'ψώχω', 'psōchō', 1, 'to rub in pieces, as the ears of grain, Lk. 6:1*'),
(5339, 'ω', 6043, '5599', 'ὦ', 'ō', 17, 'O!, Mt. 15:28; Mk. 9:19; Acts 1:1; Rom. 2:1, 3; 11:33'),
(5340, 'ωδε', 6045, '5602', 'ὧδε', 'hōde', 61, 'here, in this place, Mt. 12:6, 41; ὡδε ἠ ὡδε, here or there, Mt. 24:23; τὰ ὡδε, the state of things here, Col. 4:9; met. herein, in this thing, Rev. 13:10, 18; to this place, Mt. 8:29; 14:18'),
(5341, 'ωδη', 6046, '5603', 'ὧδή', ' ōdē', 7, 'an ode, song, hymn, Eph. 5:19; Col. 3:16; Rev. 5:9; 14:3; 15:3*'),
(5342, 'ωδιν', 6047, '5604', 'ὠδίν', 'ōdin', 4, 'the spasms or pains, of a woman in travail, a birth pang, 1 Thess. 5:3; pl. met. birth throes, preliminary troubles to the development of a catastrophe, Mt. 24:8; Mk. 13:8; from the Hebrew, a stringent band, a snare, noose, Acts 2:24*'),
(5343, 'ωδινω', 6048, '5605', 'ὠδίνω', 'ōdinō', 3, 'to be in travail, Gal. 4:27; Rev. 12:2; met. to travail with, suffer birth pangs, to make effort to bring to spiritual birth, Gal. 4:19* '),
(5344, 'ωμος', 6049, '5606', 'ὦμος', 'ōmos', 2, 'the shoulder, Mt. 23:4; Lk. 15:5*'),
(5345, 'ωνεομαι', 6050, '5608', 'ὠνέομαι', 'ōneomai', 1, 'to buy, purchase, Acts 7:16*'),
(5346, 'ωον', 6051, '5609', 'ὧόν', 'ōon', 1, 'an egg, Lk. 11:12*'),
(5347, 'ωρα', 6052, '5610', 'ὥρα', 'hōra', 106, 'a limited portion of time, marked out by part of a settled routine or train of circumstances; a season of the year; time of day, Mt. 14:15; Mk. 6:35; 11:11; an hour, Mt. 20:3; Jn. 11:9; in NT an eventful season, 1 Jn. 2:18 (2x); Rev. 3:10; 14:7; due time, Jn. 16:21; Rom. 13:11; a destined period, hour, Mt. 26:45; Mk. 14:35; Jn. 2:4; 7:30; a short period, Mt. 26:40; Jn. 5:35; 2 Cor. 7:8; Gal. 2:5; 1 Thess. 2:17; Phlm. 15; a point of time, time, Mt. 8:13; 24:42; Lk. 2:38 '),
